{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":944,"text":"I remember when I first found out"},{"time":2866,"text":"I was going to speak at a TED conference."},{"time":4929,"text":"I ran across the hall\nto one of my classrooms"},{"time":7064,"text":"to inform my students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8517,"text":"\"Guess what, guys?"},{"time":9789,"text":"I've been asked to give a TED Talk.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":11891,"text":"The reaction wasn't one I quite expected."},{"time":13946,"text":"The whole room went silent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17134,"text":"\"A TED Talk? You mean, like the one\nyou made us watch on grit?"},{"time":20118,"text":"Or the one with the scientist that did\nthis really awesome thing with robots?\""},{"time":23837,"text":"Muhammad asked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25027,"text":"\"Yes, just like that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":27137,"text":"\"But Coach, those people\nare really important and smart.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":30095,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32196,"text":"\"I know that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":34793,"text":"\"But Coach, why are you speaking?\nYou hate public speaking.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":39071,"text":"\"I do,\" I admitted,"},{"time":42334,"text":"\"But it's important that I speak about us,\nthat I speak about your journeys,"},{"time":45957,"text":"about my journey."},{"time":47140,"text":"People need to know.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":49098,"text":"The students at the all-refugee\nschool that I founded"},{"time":51835,"text":"decided to end with some\nwords of encouragement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54251,"text":"\"Cool! It better be good, Coach.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":56094,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58818,"text":"There are 65.3 million people\nwho have been forcibly displaced"},{"time":62400,"text":"from their homes because\nof war or persecution."},{"time":66035,"text":"The largest number,\n11 million, are from Syria."},{"time":69963,"text":"33,952 people flee their homes daily."},{"time":76846,"text":"The vast majority remain in refugee camps,"},{"time":80068,"text":"whose conditions cannot be defined\nas humane under anyone's definition."},{"time":84686,"text":"We are participating\nin the degradation of humans."},{"time":92750,"text":"Never have we had numbers this high."},{"time":94555,"text":"This is the highest number\nof refugees since World War II."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98415,"text":"Now, let me tell you why this issue\nis so important to me."},{"time":102144,"text":"I am an Arab. I am an immigrant."},{"time":106024,"text":"I am a Muslim."},{"time":108006,"text":"I've also spent the last 12 years\nof my life working with refugees."},{"time":111804,"text":"Oh -- and I'm also gay."},{"time":113270,"text":"It makes me really popular these days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115194,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117109,"text":"But I am the daughter of a refugee."},{"time":120056,"text":"My grandmother fled Syria in 1964\nduring the first Assad regime."},{"time":124578,"text":"She was three months pregnant\nwhen she packed up a suitcase,"},{"time":128049,"text":"piled in her five children\nand drove to neighboring Jordan,"},{"time":131167,"text":"not knowing what the future held\nfor her and her family."},{"time":134203,"text":"My grandfather decided to stay,\nnot believing it was that bad."},{"time":138562,"text":"He followed her a month later,\nafter his brothers were tortured"},{"time":142060,"text":"and his factory was taken over\nby the government."},{"time":145039,"text":"They rebuilt their lives\nstarting from scratch"},{"time":147257,"text":"and eventually became independently\nwealthy Jordanian citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151969,"text":"I was born in Jordan 11 years later."},{"time":155431,"text":"It was really important to my grandmother\nfor us to know our history"},{"time":158765,"text":"and our journey."},{"time":160883,"text":"I was eight years old when she took me\nto visit my first refugee camp."},{"time":164524,"text":"I didn't understand why."},{"time":166636,"text":"I didn't know why\nit was so important to her"},{"time":168791,"text":"for us to go."},{"time":170265,"text":"I remember walking into the camp\nholding her hand,"},{"time":173228,"text":"and her saying, \"Go play with the kids,\""},{"time":175221,"text":"while she visited\nwith the women in the camp."},{"time":178606,"text":"I didn't want to."},{"time":179842,"text":"These kids weren't like me."},{"time":181282,"text":"They were poor. They lived in a camp."},{"time":183084,"text":"I refused."},{"time":184448,"text":"She knelt down beside me\nand firmly said, \"Go."},{"time":187438,"text":"And don't come back until you've played."},{"time":189616,"text":"Don't ever think people are beneath you"},{"time":191680,"text":"or that you have nothing\nto learn from others.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":194520,"text":"I reluctantly went."},{"time":195993,"text":"I never wanted to disappoint\nmy grandmother."},{"time":199475,"text":"I returned a few hours later,"},{"time":200896,"text":"having spent some time playing soccer\nwith the kids in the camp."},{"time":206039,"text":"We walked out of the camp,"},{"time":207340,"text":"and I was excitedly telling her\nwhat a great time I had"},{"time":210059,"text":"and how fantastic the kids were."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213175,"text":"\"Haram!\" I said in Arabic. \"Poor them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":216648,"text":"\"Haram on us,\" she said,\nusing the word's different meaning,"},{"time":219759,"text":"that we were sinning."},{"time":222002,"text":"\"Don't feel sorry for them;\nbelieve in them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":226351,"text":"It wasn't until I left my country\nof origin for the United States"},{"time":229794,"text":"that I realized the impact of her words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233187,"text":"After my college graduation, I applied for\nand was granted political asylum,"},{"time":236885,"text":"based on being a member of a social group."},{"time":239710,"text":"Some people may not realize this,"},{"time":241424,"text":"but you can still get the death penalty\nin some countries for being gay."},{"time":247077,"text":"I had to give up my Jordanian citizenship."},{"time":249145,"text":"That was the hardest decision\nI've ever had to make,"},{"time":251618,"text":"but I had no other choice."},{"time":257387,"text":"The point is,"},{"time":259506,"text":"when you find yourself choosing\nbetween home and survival,"},{"time":262606,"text":"the question \"Where are you from?\"\nbecomes very loaded."},{"time":266772,"text":"A Syrian woman who I recently met\nat a refugee camp in Greece"},{"time":270063,"text":"articulated it best,"},{"time":271355,"text":"when she recalled the exact moment\nshe realized she had to flee Aleppo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275277,"text":"\"I looked out the window\nand there was nothing."},{"time":277559,"text":"It was all rubble."},{"time":279593,"text":"There were no stores, no streets,\nno schools. Everything was gone."},{"time":284006,"text":"I had been in my apartment for months,"},{"time":286077,"text":"listening to bombs drop\nand watching people die."},{"time":289771,"text":"But I always thought it would get better,"},{"time":293028,"text":"that no one could force me to leave,"},{"time":295126,"text":"no one could take my home away from me."},{"time":297795,"text":"And I don't know why it was that morning,\nbut when I looked outside,"},{"time":301091,"text":"I realized if I didn't leave,\nmy three young children would die."},{"time":304253,"text":"And so we left."},{"time":305666,"text":"We left because we had to,\nnot because we wanted to."},{"time":308694,"text":"There was no choice,\" she said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311978,"text":"It's kind of hard to believe\nthat you belong"},{"time":314280,"text":"when you don't have a home,"},{"time":315768,"text":"when your country of origin rejects you\nbecause of fear or persecution,"},{"time":319798,"text":"or the city that you grew up in\nis completely destroyed."},{"time":324805,"text":"I didn't feel like I had a home."},{"time":326860,"text":"I was no longer a Jordanian citizen,"},{"time":329341,"text":"but I wasn't American, either."},{"time":331643,"text":"I felt a kind of loneliness"},{"time":333405,"text":"that is still hard\nto put into words today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336781,"text":"After college, I desperately needed\nto find a place to call home."},{"time":340546,"text":"I bounced around from state to state"},{"time":342286,"text":"and eventually ended up in North Carolina."},{"time":344745,"text":"Kindhearted people who felt sorry for me"},{"time":347413,"text":"offered to pay rent"},{"time":349405,"text":"or buy me a meal or a suit\nfor my new interview."},{"time":352743,"text":"It just made me feel\nmore isolated and incapable."},{"time":356481,"text":"It wasn't until I met Miss Sarah,"},{"time":358319,"text":"a Southern Baptist who took me in\nat my lowest and gave me a job,"},{"time":362079,"text":"that I started to believe in myself."},{"time":364695,"text":"Miss Sarah owned a diner\nin the mountains of North Carolina."},{"time":369856,"text":"I assumed, because\nof my privileged upbringing"},{"time":372049,"text":"and my Seven Sister education,"},{"time":373592,"text":"that she would ask me\nto manage the restaurant."},{"time":375820,"text":"I was wrong."},{"time":377972,"text":"I started off washing dishes,"},{"time":379699,"text":"cleaning toilets and working the grill."},{"time":382247,"text":"I was humbled; I was shown\nthe value of hard work."},{"time":385356,"text":"But most importantly,\nI felt valued and embraced."},{"time":388924,"text":"I celebrated Christmas with her family,"},{"time":390828,"text":"and she attempted to observe\nRamadan with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394236,"text":"I remember being very nervous\nabout coming out to her --"},{"time":396930,"text":"after all, she was a Southern Baptist."},{"time":398996,"text":"I sat on the couch next to her"},{"time":400480,"text":"and I said, \"Miss Sarah,\nyou know that I'm gay.\""},{"time":403035,"text":"Her response is one\nthat I will never forget."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405715,"text":"\"That's fine, honey.\nJust don't be a slut.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":407938,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":411134,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":413833,"text":"I eventually moved to Atlanta,\nstill trying to find my home."},{"time":420261,"text":"My journey took a strange turn\nthree years later,"},{"time":422664,"text":"after I met a group of refugee kids\nplaying soccer outside."},{"time":426318,"text":"I'd made a wrong turn\ninto this apartment complex,"},{"time":428882,"text":"and I saw these kids\noutside playing soccer."},{"time":431496,"text":"They were playing barefoot\nwith a raggedy soccer ball"},{"time":434083,"text":"and rocks set up as goals."},{"time":435559,"text":"I watched them for about an hour,"},{"time":437283,"text":"and after that I was smiling."},{"time":439296,"text":"The boys reminded me of home."},{"time":441368,"text":"They reminded me of the way\nI grew up playing soccer"},{"time":443870,"text":"in the streets of Jordan,\nwith my brothers and cousins."},{"time":447792,"text":"I eventually joined their game."},{"time":449817,"text":"They were a little skeptical\nabout letting me join it,"},{"time":452684,"text":"because according to them,\ngirls don't know how to play."},{"time":455370,"text":"But obviously I did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456740,"text":"I asked them if they had\never played on a team."},{"time":459008,"text":"They said they hadn't,\nbut that they would love to."},{"time":461931,"text":"I gradually won them over,\nand we formed our first team."},{"time":465851,"text":"This group of kids would give me\na crash course in refugees, poverty"},{"time":471997,"text":"and humanity."},{"time":474375,"text":"Three brothers from Afghanistan --\nRoohullah, Noorullah and Zabiullah --"},{"time":477954,"text":"played a major role in that."},{"time":480380,"text":"I showed up late to practice one day\nto find the field completely deserted."},{"time":483972,"text":"I was really worried."},{"time":485177,"text":"My team loved to practice."},{"time":486812,"text":"It wasn't like them to miss practice."},{"time":489443,"text":"I got out of my car, and two kids\nran out from behind a dumpster,"},{"time":492555,"text":"waving their hands frantically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495095,"text":"\"Coach, Rooh got beat up. He got jumped."},{"time":497166,"text":"There was blood everywhere.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":498768,"text":"\"What do you mean?\nWhat do you mean he got beat up?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":501247,"text":"\"These bad kids came\nand beat him up, Coach."},{"time":503344,"text":"Everybody left. They were all scared.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":505594,"text":"We hopped into my car\nand drove over to Rooh's apartment."},{"time":508336,"text":"I knocked on the door, and Noor opened it."},{"time":511589,"text":"\"Where's Rooh? I need\nto talk to him, see if he's OK.\""},{"time":514365,"text":"\"He's in his room, Coach.\nHe's refusing to come out.\""},{"time":517325,"text":"I knocked on the door."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518516,"text":"\"Rooh, come on out. I need to talk to you."},{"time":520966,"text":"I need to see if you're OK\nor if we need to go to the hospital.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":524041,"text":"He came out."},{"time":525216,"text":"He had a big gash on his head,\na split lip,"},{"time":528019,"text":"and he was physically shaken."},{"time":530514,"text":"I was looking at him,"},{"time":531871,"text":"and I asked the boys\nto call for their mom,"},{"time":534454,"text":"because I needed to go\nto the hospital with him."},{"time":536890,"text":"They called for their mom."},{"time":538608,"text":"She came out."},{"time":540239,"text":"I had my back turned to her,\nand she started screaming in Farsi."},{"time":544577,"text":"The boys fell to the ground laughing."},{"time":546676,"text":"I was very confused,"},{"time":547852,"text":"because there was nothing\nfunny about this."},{"time":550390,"text":"They explained to me that she said,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552414,"text":"\"You told me your coach\nwas a Muslim and a woman.\""},{"time":555252,"text":"From behind, I didn't appear\nto be either to her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557645,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":561302,"text":"\"I am Muslim,\" I said, turning to her."},{"time":563562,"text":"\"Ašhadu ʾan lā ʾilāha ʾilla (A)llāh,\""},{"time":565517,"text":"reciting the Muslim declaration of faith."},{"time":568587,"text":"Confused,"},{"time":571208,"text":"and perhaps maybe a little bit reassured,"},{"time":573222,"text":"she realized that yes,"},{"time":574401,"text":"I, this American-acting,\nshorts-wearing, non-veiled woman,"},{"time":577716,"text":"was indeed a Muslim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580166,"text":"Their family had fled the Taliban."},{"time":583687,"text":"Hundreds of people in their village"},{"time":585415,"text":"were murdered."},{"time":586685,"text":"Their father was taken in by the Taliban,"},{"time":588922,"text":"only to return a few months later,\na shell of the man he once was."},{"time":594738,"text":"The family escaped to Pakistan,"},{"time":597173,"text":"and the two older boys,\nage eight and 10 at the time,"},{"time":600765,"text":"wove rugs for 10 hours a day\nto provide for their family."},{"time":604926,"text":"They were so excited when they found out\nthat they had been approved"},{"time":608707,"text":"to resettle in the United States,"},{"time":611223,"text":"making them the lucky 0.1 percent\nwho get to do that."},{"time":614500,"text":"They had hit the jackpot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616930,"text":"Their story is not unique."},{"time":619085,"text":"Every refugee family I have worked with\nhas had some version of this."},{"time":623017,"text":"I work with kids"},{"time":625206,"text":"who have seen their mothers raped,\ntheir fathers' fingers sliced off."},{"time":629089,"text":"One kid saw a bullet\nput in his grandmother's head,"},{"time":632068,"text":"because she refused to let the rebels\ntake him to be a child soldier."},{"time":637943,"text":"Their journeys are haunting."},{"time":639940,"text":"But what I get to see every day\nis hope, resilience, determination,"},{"time":645738,"text":"a love of life"},{"time":646947,"text":"and appreciation for being able\nto rebuild their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651607,"text":"I was at the boys' apartment one night,"},{"time":653756,"text":"when the mom came home\nafter cleaning 18 hotel rooms in one day."},{"time":658590,"text":"She sat down, and Noor rubbed her feet,"},{"time":661679,"text":"saying that he was going to take care\nof her once he graduated."},{"time":664778,"text":"She smiled from exhaustion."},{"time":666296,"text":"\"God is good. Life is good.\nWe are lucky to be here.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":671001,"text":"In the last two years, we have seen\nan escalating anti-refugee sentiment."},{"time":676219,"text":"It's global."},{"time":678579,"text":"The numbers continue to grow\nbecause we do nothing to prevent it"},{"time":681847,"text":"and nothing to stop it."},{"time":683572,"text":"The issue shouldn't be stopping refugees\nfrom coming into our countries."},{"time":687148,"text":"The issue should be\nnot forcing them to leave their own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690160,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":706510,"text":"Sorry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707859,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":717917,"text":"How much more suffering,"},{"time":720466,"text":"how much more suffering must we take?"},{"time":723255,"text":"How many more people need to be\nforced out of their homes"},{"time":726050,"text":"before we say, \"Enough!\"?"},{"time":727455,"text":"A hundred million?"},{"time":729125,"text":"Not only do we shame,\nblame and reject them"},{"time":733245,"text":"for atrocities that they had\nabsolutely nothing to do with,"},{"time":737012,"text":"we re-traumatize them,"},{"time":738191,"text":"when we're supposed to be welcoming\nthem into our countries."},{"time":743291,"text":"We strip them of their dignity\nand treat them like criminals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746618,"text":"I had a student in my office\na couple of weeks ago."},{"time":749348,"text":"She's originally from Iraq."},{"time":751188,"text":"She broke down crying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753595,"text":"\"Why do they hate us?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":755247,"text":"\"Who hates you?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":756445,"text":"\"Everyone; everyone hates us\nbecause we are refugees,"},{"time":759240,"text":"because we are Muslim.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":762019,"text":"In the past, I was able\nto reassure my students"},{"time":764379,"text":"that the majority of the world\ndoes not hate refugees."},{"time":767040,"text":"But this time I couldn't."},{"time":768868,"text":"I couldn't explain to her why someone\ntried to rip off her mother's hijab"},{"time":772372,"text":"when they were grocery shopping,"},{"time":774181,"text":"or why a player on an opposing\nteam called her a terrorist"},{"time":777449,"text":"and told her to go back\nwhere she came from."},{"time":779956,"text":"I couldn't reassure her"},{"time":781742,"text":"that her father's ultimate life sacrifice"},{"time":784105,"text":"by serving in the United States\nmilitary as an interpreter"},{"time":787249,"text":"would make her more valued\nas an American citizen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791051,"text":"We take in so few refugees worldwide."},{"time":794949,"text":"We resettle less than 0.1 percent."},{"time":798778,"text":"That 0.1 percent benefits us\nmore than them."},{"time":802797,"text":"It dumbfounds me how the word \"refugee\"\nis considered something to be dirty,"},{"time":806607,"text":"something to be ashamed of."},{"time":808244,"text":"They have nothing to be ashamed of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813827,"text":"We have seen advances\nin every aspect of our lives --"},{"time":816574,"text":"except our humanity."},{"time":818523,"text":"There are 65.3 million people\nwho have been forced out of their homes"},{"time":822986,"text":"because of war --"},{"time":824685,"text":"the largest number in history."},{"time":827110,"text":"We are the ones who should be ashamed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829712,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830891,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}